    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA207-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu notumalar varaivuḻit (ET: vantuḻi) tōḻi cevilikku aṟattoṭu niṉṟatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante stood up to virtue (~ revealed the truth) to the foster mother when there was a marriage [offer] by strangers.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA207">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            kaṇṭal vēlik kaḻicūḻ paṭappai</l>
<l>            muṇṭakam vēynta kuṟiyiṟaik kurampaik</l>
<l>            koḻumīṉ koḷpavar pākkaṅ kalleṉa</l>
<l>            neṭuntēr paṇṇi varalā ṉātē</l>
<l>            kuṉṟat taṉṉa kuvavumaṇa ṉīnti </l>
<l>            vantaṉar peyarvarko ṟāmē yalka</l>
<l>            liḷaiyaru mutiyaruṅ kiḷaiyuṭaṉ kuḻīik</l>
<l>            kōṭcuṟā veṟinteṉac curuṅkiya narampiṉ</l>
<l>            muṭimutir paratavar maṭamoḻik kuṟumakaḷ</l>
<l>            valaiyun tūṇṭilum paṟṟip peruṅkāṟ </l>
<l>            ṟiraiyeḻu pauva muṉṉiya</l>
<l>            kolaiveñ ciṟāar pāṟpaṭ ṭaṉaḷē.</l>
            
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>[His] coming does not end, the long chariot prepared,</l>
<l rend="indent">noisily, to the village of those who are taking rich fish,</l>
<l rend="indent2">in huts with short-eaved [roofs] covered in Muṇṭakam</l>
<l rend="indent2">[and] gardens surrounded by backwaters with mangrove fences.</l>
<l>Has he come, crossing the sands heaped-like hills,</l>
<l>[and now] goes [back again all by] himself?</l>
<l>The little daughter with innocent words of the fishermen,</l>
<l rend="indent">re-fashioning the knots [of their nets] with shrunken fibre(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">curuṅkiya narampiṉ muṭi mutir</term>: this phrase is semantically elusive as it is syntactically unmarked. Thus the interpretation of T.V.G. (who agrees to reading <term xml:lang="ta">narampu</term> instead of <term xml:lang="ta">nāmpu</term>) along with the commentaries.</note>,</l>
<l>because they had thrown up the killing shark,</l>
<l rend="indent">crowding at night with [their] relations, young [and] old,</l>
<l>– the fate of [their] children, keen on killing,</l>
<l rend="indent">to approach the ocean where waves rise in the great wind,</l>
<l rend="indent2">[their] fishing net and hook tight in hand,</l>
<l rend="indent3">has befallen her [too].</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
